{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-a36e3bf0298d8d69", "type": "tool_result", "content": "# SALAD-VAE: Semantic Audio Compression with Language-Audio Distillation\narXiv: 2510.07592\nAuthors: Sebastian Braun, Hannes Gamper, Dimitra Emmanouilidou\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A continuous frequency-domain audio VAE is proposed that compresses audio into a highly compact latent space with a low frame rate of 7.8 Hz.\n  2. Generalization across diverse audio domains is improved by augmenting training with on-the-fly polyphonic data mixing and random input degradations.\n  3. A contrastive learning technique utilizing both a contrastive loss and a CLAP-based embedding distillation loss is introduced to enhance semantic representation and disentanglement.\n  4. Audio captioning and zero-shot classification capabilities are enabled by repurposing the trained CLAP projection layer to map VAE embeddings into the joint text-audio space.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-VAE, 压缩/语义声学-语义", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "1e828321-a6e9-41cf-8e6e-030da376db66", "uuid": "7539c2a5-5818-4cd8-a0e1-19fa14a14760", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T12:13:51.286Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "# SALAD-VAE: Semantic Audio Compression with Language-Audio Distillation\narXiv: 2510.07592\nAuthors: Sebastian Braun, Hannes Gamper, Dimitra Emmanouilidou\nYear: 2025 | Venue: \nTopic: codec_vae\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A continuous frequency-domain audio VAE is proposed that compresses audio into a highly compact latent space with a low frame rate of 7.8 Hz.\n  2. Generalization across diverse audio domains is improved by augmenting training with on-the-fly polyphonic data mixing and random input degradations.\n  3. A contrastive learning technique utilizing both a contrastive loss and a CLAP-based embedding distillation loss is introduced to enhance semantic representation and disentanglement.\n  4. Audio captioning and zero-shot classification capabilities are enabled by repurposing the trained CLAP projection layer to map VAE embeddings into the joint text-audio space.\n\nTags: 压缩, 压缩/量化-VAE, 压缩/语义声学-语义", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
